main event: Several persons reported seeing a round or circular object, silent in operation and displaying no lights, in Economy, Pennsylvania on May 28, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 15 minutes and was first seen around 9:45 p.m. on May 28, 1965.
The object was described as appearing quite large in the sky, with what appeared to be rotating or turning parts on each end of the sphere.
The object was observed to be dipped at an approximate 15-degree angle, showing a dimensional view.
No photographs of the object were taken.
The Air Force concluded that the characteristics of the sighting indicated that an aircraft moving at high speed, providing inadequate visual observation time, could account for the phenomena.
sighted object: a round or circular object, silent in operation and displaying no lights
